Brazil  has become a net importer of
ethanol, particularly from the U.S., Rob Coviello, head of
global sugar trading at  Bunge Ltd. (BG) , said today at a conference
in  London . Brazil may import the biofuel in the next four to
five years, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
